    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - HOOD STOP ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HOOD STOP ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>Hood height adjustment at the cowl and rear edge of hood is adjusted by moving the hood stop either up or
            down.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900850" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900850.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 50. Hood Stop (Drivers Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CAB STRUCTURE SIDE POST</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DRIVERS SIDE DOOR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FOUR MOUNTING BOLTS AND LOCK WASHERS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HOOD STOP BUSHING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch hood and tilt hood forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To adjust hood in either direction, loosen the four bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900850">Figure 50, Item 3</hotlnk>) located at the hood stop bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the bracket upward or down to set desired height.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the hood and rest hood on hood stop bushings. Check rear edge alignment with cowl.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise the hood and Re-tighten the bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900850">Figure 50, Item 3</hotlnk>) to secure the hood stop at the desired location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The same procedure should be applied to adjust the opposite side of hood.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten to 147 to 181 lbf-ft (200 to 245 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
